olive oil
1 carrot
1 parsnip
1 beetroot
2 clove garlic
1 tin lentils
1 tsp honey
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet flaked almonds
1 packet chicken breast
15 g butter
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 packet Dijon mustard
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut carrot and parsnip into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into small chunks. Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

TIP: Beetroot stays firm when cooked. It's done when you can pierce it with a fork.

While the veggies are roasting, finely chop garlic. Drain and rinse lentils. In a small bowl, combine Dijon mustard, the honey, a splash of water and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season and stir to combine. Set aside.

TIP: Add more or less vinegar to taste.

Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

Place your hand flat on top of each chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks. In a medium bowl, combine chicken, Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a plate.

TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium
heat with the butter and a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
lentils and garlic, tossing, until warmed through
and fragrant, 2-3 minutes. Remove from heat, then
stir through roasted veggies and Dijon dressing.
Add salad leaves and gently toss to combine.
Season to taste.

Slice spiced chicken. Divide lentil roast veggie salad between bowls and top with chicken. Garnish with flaked almonds. Serve with dill & parsley mayonnaise.